To iterate through your 2D array, don&#39;t use `multiGrid[0].length` (for `i` loop) or `multiGrid[1].length` (for `j` loop). Instead use these respectively: `multiGrid.length` and `multiGrid[i].length`. After all, a Two Dimensional Array in Java is an Array of Arrays. There is no law that states that the inner Arrays all need to have the same length.

To display something that might resemble a multiplication table you can use the `System.out.printf()` method, for example:

    public static void printGrid(int[][] multiGrid) {
        // Rows...  
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; multiGrid.length; i++) { 
            // Columns...
            for (int j = 0; j &lt; multiGrid[i].length; j++) { 
                System.out.printf(&quot;%-5s&quot;, multiGrid[i][j]);
